Explanation:

- The GET /hello handler in starter.py returns Book.get(one=True).
- The Book model (app/api/v1/model/book.py) inherits from InfoCrud and defines columns: id (Integer), title (String), author (String), summary (String), image (String).
- InfoCrud (in app/lin/interface.py) injects create_time and update_time (DateTime), and also defines delete_time and is_deleted but InfoCrud._set_fields sets _exclude = ["delete_time", "is_deleted"]. The MixinJSONSerializer (app/lin/db.py) controls the JSON serializable fields and will exclude delete_time and is_deleted from the serialized output.
- Therefore a successful response (HTTP 200) will return a single Book object serialized to JSON containing these fields: id, title, author, summary, image, create_time, update_time. create_time and update_time are datetime values and are represented as strings with date-time format.
- Include a generic 500 Internal Server Error response object for unexpected failures; the project commonly uses error responses with a message and numeric code, so the schema for 500 is an object with message (string) and code (integer).

